                                    <label opaque="NO" userInteractionEnabled="NO" contentMode="left" horizontalHuggingPriority="251" verticalHuggingPriority="251" textAlignment="center" lineBreakMode="tailTruncation" numberOfLines="28" baselineAdjustment="alignBaselines" adjustsFontSizeToFit="NO" translatesAutoresizingMaskIntoConstraints="NO" id="LxF-FZ-MvA">
                                        <rect key="frame" x="0.0" y="310" width="361" height="426.33333333333326"/>
                                        <mutableString key="text">Ingredients: 2-3 lbs chicken breasts (or thighs), 1 jar (16 oz) salsa, 1 block (8 oz) cream cheese (optional, for creaminess), Tortillas or rice for serving.
Instructions:Prep the Chicken: Place the chicken breasts or thighs in the bottom of a slow cooker. Season with salt and pepper if desired, although the salsa often provides enough flavor.
Add Salsa: Pour the entire jar of salsa over the chicken, ensuring it is well-covered.
Slow Cook: Cover and cook on Low for 4–6 hours or High for 2–3 hours.
Shred: Once the chicken is tender and easily pulls apart, remove it to a bowl and shred it with two forks.
Add Cream Cheese 
Combine: Return the shredded chicken to the pot and stir to coat.
Serve: Serve hot on tortillas, over rice, or with chips.</mutableString>
                                        <fontDescription key="fontDescription" type="system" pointSize="17"/>
                                        <nil key="textColor"/>
                                        <nil key="highlightedColor"/>
                                    </label>
